  <part id="Prolog">

    <title>Prolog Rule Programming</title>

    <faq id="how-install">
      <question>
        How do I import RUGE Prolog libraries?
      </question>
      <answer>
        <p>Set file_search_path, e.g.:</p>

        <source>
user:file_search_path(ruge,'c:/some/where').
:- include(ruge(common)).
        </source>
        <p>In order to avoid hard-coding the path in Prolog code, the path can be retrieved from the environment
        or as a -DRUGE_HOME=path argument on the command line.</p>
		<source>
user:file_search_path(ruge,'$RUGE_HOME').
:- include(ruge(common)).
		</source>
      </answer>
    </faq>

  </part>

  <part id="Java">

    <title>Java Rule Execution</title>

    <faq id="how-install">
      <question>
        How is the RUGE Java component different from the RUGE Prolog component?
      </question>
      <answer>
        <p>The Java component is for executing tests. The RUGE component generates tests.</p>
      </answer>
    </faq>

